  <div class="fourteen wide column text-weight-bold text-size-medium text-uppercase" style="color: #d7554e;">
    rules and regulations
  </div>
  <div class="fourteen wide column text-weight-bold text-size-medium text-uppercase" style="color: #4A90E2">
    a) fees
  </div>
  <div class="fourteen wide column text-weight-bold padding-no-top">
    <ul>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Monthly fees should be paid before the 10th of every month. A fine of Rs 10 will be charged per day if paid after 10th.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Yearly fees should be paid by 15th march of every year. A fine of Rs 100 will be charged per month if delayed.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Bargaining regarding school fees or any other fee is strictly prohibited.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="fourteen wide column text-weight-bold text-size-medium text-uppercase" style="color: #4A90E2">
    b) attire
  </div>
  <div class="fourteen wide column text-weight-bold padding-no-top">
    <ul>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students are expected to wear the prescribed school uniform. Any modifications/additions to the uniform is will not be permitted.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students must be neat in appearance. Boys are not allowed to keep facial hair and boys with facial hair will be required to be clean-shaven.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Boys should have a short and neat haircut. Their hair should be neatly combed. Spiked/pointed or any kind of styled hair will not be allowed.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Girls with shoulder length hair or longer should tie their hair. The hair/fringe should not touch the eyebrows. Girls should only use black/maroon/white hair bands, hair clips or scrunchies.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">No fanciful hair accessories will be allowed.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students should retain the natural colour of their hair. They are not allowed to have colore treated hair.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students are not allowed to wear jewellery to school. Girls are only allowed to wear a pair of small stud earrings, one on each ear. The colour of the stud earrings should be confined to gold, silver or black.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students are not allowed to wear coloured contact lenses.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Watches containing loud animation and/or game features that can cause distraction in class will not be allowed.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="fourteen wide column text-weight-bold text-size-medium text-uppercase" style="color: #4A90E2">
    c) punctuality
  </div>
  <div class="fourteen wide column text-weight-bold padding-no-top">
    <ul>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">All Students are expected to be present at school on time.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">All Students are strongly encouraged to be present at the assembly area by 9:10am so that the morning assembly can be started promptly by 9:15am.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students arriving to school after the morning assembly starts will be treated as absent.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students are strictly forbidden to leave the school premises during school hours without written permission from the concerned teacher.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="fourteen wide column text-weight-bold text-size-medium text-uppercase" style="color: #4A90E2">
    d) serious offences
  </div>
  <div class="fourteen wide column text-weight-bold padding-no-top">
    <ul>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students should not vandalize or deface any school property e.g. school building, furniture, fire alarm panels, etc.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">STudents should not leave the school premises during curriculum or lunch breaks without the permission of the principal/vice principal/form teacher/subject teacher.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students who are in school before/after curriculum hours for supplementary lessons,/remedial lessons/CCAs etc are not allowed to leave the school premises unless they have a written note from their parents.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students are not allowed to have any kind of weapons in their possession. They are also not allowed to bring any weapon-like item which can be harmful intentionally/not to others.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students must not play truant.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students are not forbidden from using any kind of abusive/vulgar language.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students should not be involved in stealing, fighting, extortion or smoking.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students should not be defiant/rude to the staff/teachers of the school.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="fourteen wide column text-weight-bold text-size-medium text-uppercase" style="color: #4A90E2">
    e) cellphones
  </div>
  <div class="fourteen wide column text-weight-bold padding-no-top">
    <ul>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students are not allowed to bring cellphones to school unless under special circumstances with written approval from school.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Those with approval are not allowed to use the cellphones within the school premises. They can use them on the way to school or on the way home.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">If any student is caught using cellphonrs within the school premises, the cellphone will be confiscated and parents will be asked to come to the school to collect it and henceforth the student will not be allowed to have a cellphone in school.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="fourteen wide column text-weight-bold text-size-medium text-uppercase" style="color: #4A90E2">
    f)  leave
  </div>
  <div class="fourteen wide column text-weight-bold padding-no-top">
    <ul>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">If a student continues to be absent for 5 working days without any valid leave application his/her name shall be struck off from the attendance roll of the school. Re=admission may be done after paying admission fee.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students are expected to Send leave applications through diary.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Absence from school must be explained either by producing a medical certificate or a letter from the parent or guardian.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="fourteen wide column text-weight-bold text-size-medium text-uppercase" style="color: #4A90E2">
    g)  other rules
  </div>
  <div class="fourteen wide column text-weight-bold padding-no-top">
    <ul>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students are not allowed to bring any valuable ornaments in the school. The school will not be responsible for any loss of such items.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">The students who fail in the same class for two years consecutively then his/her name will be struck off from the school attendance list.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Visitors, parents/guardians are not allowed to interview the teachers and students during the class hours without permission. In all cases the principal should be contacted.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Parents intending to withdraw their children from the school must bring it to the notice of the principal in written a month before and pay all the fees and other dues before securing the transfer certificate.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">All the text books and other stationary items will be supplied by the school on cash payment in advance.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="fourteen wide column text-weight-bold text-size-medium text-uppercase" style="color: #4A90E2">
    h)  possible consequences for non-compliance to school rules
  </div>
  <div class="fourteen wide column text-weight-bold padding-no-top">
    <ul>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Verbal warning by school staff.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">The matter will be brought to the Principal’s/Vice Principal’s/HOD Student Management’s/Year Head’s and Assistant Year Head’s attention for further action.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students will not be allowed to join other students during break hours and are expected to bring their own food from home and consume in during their detention.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Parents intending to withdraw their children from the school must bring it to the notice of the principal in written a month before and pay all the fees and other dues before securing the transfer certificate.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Students are expected to keep the school premises clean. They will have to pick litter within the school premises or clean canteen tables after having lunch.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Suspension from school.</li>
      <li class="margin-bottom-ten">Caning will not be ruled out for serious offences.</li>
    </ul>
